## Workday user research sources

**Hub:** [`docs/workday-user-research/README.md`](../../docs/workday-user-research/README.md) (PDFs + index).

When drafting **Audience / Personas** and JTBD-related narrative:

1. Read **`docs/workday-user-research/README.md`** and open the **relevant PDF(s)** for the users in scope.
2. Map **Primary / Secondary / Tertiary** personas explicitly, for example:
   - **HR Professional (Recruiting)** — supplemental JTBD PDF + [`docs/jtbd-recruiting-hr-professional-and-manager.md`](../../docs/jtbd-recruiting-hr-professional-and-manager.md) for verbatim JTBD lines
   - **Frontline Manager** — `Frontline-Manager-UX-Persona-V1.pdf` when the initiative targets frontline hiring managers
   - **External Candidate** — `External-Candidate-UX-Persona-V1.pdf` for candidate-facing or career-site scope
3. Keep alignment with **[`docs/experience-principles.md`](../../docs/experience-principles.md)** (Empower, Trust, Grow) and the curated JTBD markdown where recruiter/manager jobs apply.

Cite in the PRD which sources informed personas (e.g. one line under **Audience / Personas**: *Persona depth from docs/workday-user-research/ …*).

## Workday PRD Template

**Based on**: Interview Team Optimization Skill PRD (GA version)

**Format**: 11-page document structure with professional tone and formatting

**Key Characteristics**:
- Font: Standard (Calibri or similar)
- Tone: Professional, data-driven, strategic
- Length: Comprehensive (8-12 pages typical)
- British English spelling
- Page numbers: "X of Y" format at bottom

**CRITICAL - No Agentic Metadata**: Do NOT include pipeline IDs (GCC-E2E-NNN), HITL references, agent workflow steps, or internal tracking in the PRD header or Executive Summary. The PRD is a customer-facing professional document. Mission tracking belongs in MISSION_LOG.md only.

**Correct header format:**
```markdown
# [Feature Name] ([Release Version])
Product Requirements Document
[Month, Year]
```

**FORBIDDEN patterns in PRDs:**
- ❌ "**Pipeline:** GCC-E2E-028..."
- ❌ "HITL selection: ..."
- ❌ "PM framing applied per..."
- ❌ Any reference to agent numbers (@pmf-analyst, 105, @competitive-intel, 130, 315, 320, etc.) in body text
- ❌ "Mission GCC-E2E-NNN" in headings or prominent positions

**Acceptable internal references** (in body text only, when necessary for traceability):
- ✅ File paths to research: `research/GCC/thematic-analysis/2026-03-27-GCC-PMF-Analysis-GCC-E2E-025.md`
- ✅ "Source research: ..." with file path
- ✅ "PMF analysis (@pmf-analyst): ..." in Resources section only

```markdown
# [Feature Name] ([Release Version])
Product Requirements Document
[Month, Year]

## Executive Summary

[3-4 paragraphs covering:]

**Paragraph 1**: Workday's unique positioning and the specific feature being delivered
- Lead with "Workday is uniquely positioned to develop..."
- State the release timeline and key capability

**Paragraph 2**: Customer benefits and value
- Start with "For our customers, this feature will..."
- Quantify impact where possible (time savings, reduction in burden, quality improvements)

**Paragraph 3**: Workday business value
- Start with "For Workday, this initiative will..."
- Focus on: retention, adoption, market differentiation, revenue

**Paragraph 4** (if applicable): Additional context
- Delivery mechanism (e.g., "For GA, this Skill will feature as part of...")
- Epic references

**Epic Links:**
